#### **monthlyProjectCount Calculation (Lines 90-125):**
This is a **memoized computation** using `useMemo`:
```typescript
const monthlyProjectCount = useMemo(() => {
  if (history.length === 0) return 0;

  // Define billing cycle start (1st of current month)
  const now = new Date();
  const billingCycleStart = new Date(now.getFullYear(), now.getMonth(), 1);

  // 1. Identify creation date of each domain
  const projectCreationDates = new Map<string, Date>();

  history.forEach(h => {
    let hostname;
    try { hostname = new URL(h.url).hostname; } catch(e) { hostname = h.url; }

    const analysisDate = new Date(h.timestamp);

    if (!projectCreationDates.has(hostname)) {
      projectCreationDates.set(hostname, analysisDate);
    } else {
      // Keep the oldest date found for this domain
      if (analysisDate < projectCreationDates.get(hostname)!) {
        projectCreationDates.set(hostname, analysisDate);
      }
    }
  });

  // 2. Count only projects created after billing cycle start
  let count = 0;
  projectCreationDates.forEach((creationDate) => {
    if (creationDate >= billingCycleStart) {
      count++;
    }
  });

  return count;
}, [history]);
```

**Logic Summary:**
- Counts unique domains analyzed in the CURRENT MONTH ONLY
- Uses domain hostname as unique identifier
- Tracks oldest analysis date per domain
- Only counts projects where first analysis ≥ 1st of current month
- Used to enforce monthly quota limits

#### **handleUpgradePlan Function (Lines 361-364):**
